title: #8: R-Ladies Frankfurt: Christmas meetup
description:
Dear all,

We’re happy to invite you to the eighth meetup of R-Ladies Frankfurt group on 12th December (Thursday).

In this meetup, we’re going to discuss our favourite R tricks, functions and packages in a relaxed Christmas atmosphere.

Location:
36 Grad
Oppenheimer Landstraße 36
60596 Frankfurt am Main

What to bring? (optional for this session)
(1) laptop with
(2) pre-installed R & RStudio (https://www.rstudio.com/products/rstudio/)*
(3) motivation to meet people, and have fun to create an active R community for women!
*If you’re having issues with installation and set-up, don’t worry! We’re all here to help :)

You’re welcome no matter if you are a complete newbie to R, intermediate or professional R-user.

If you have any suggestions/questions, please feel free to get in touch: frankfurt@rladies.org

Also, follow R-Ladies Frankfurt on twitter: @RLadiesFRA (https://twitter.com/RLadiesFRA) and stay tuned for R and R-Ladies related tweets!

Know other people interested in R? Bring them along!

Please only RSVP if you can come!

Looking forward to seeing you!
R-Ladies Frankfurt

title: #6: Let’s git together: Introduction to git with github and gitkraken
description:
Dear all,

We’re happy to invite you to the sixth meetup of R-Ladies Frankfurt group on 12th September (Thursday).

In this session, we’re going to explore tools to develop reproducible workflows. In particular, we will learn about git, github, and gitkraken as well as integrate them into our daily workflow. These are an added-value to our data science toolbox, which can facilitate to share our work with our future self and team members.

Frie Preu will guide us throughout this session. Frie works as a data scientist / IT consultant at codecentric. Her journey with R started in 2012 at university. Frie really enjoys data wrangling, writing R packages, and building tools in and for R. In her free time, she volunteers as a core team member for CorrelAid, a data for good network with over 800 members.

Location:
codecentric AG
Kreuznacher Straße 30
60486 Frankfurt am Main

SPECIAL THANKS to codecentric for hosting our event!

What to bring?
(1) laptop with
(2) pre-installed R & RStudio (https://www.rstudio.com/products/rstudio/)*

title: #5 - Code together: From messy data to insightful visualizations - part 2
description:
Dear all,

We’re happy to invite you to the fifth meetup of R-Ladies Frankfurt group on 8th August (Thursday).

Last time we did the data wrangling and now we are ready to visualize our data with ggplot2, one of the core packages of the tidyverse. Let's use graphs to explore our artifical dataset and to gain information about which factors might be correlated with treatment success.
Don't worry if you missed the last session: We provide you with the data set and some exemplary code for cleaning it.

You’re welcome no matter if you are a complete newbie to R, intermediate or professional R-user, and also if you have never heard about tidyverse packages.

Afterwards, we’ll share what we achieved, our difficulties, and how we went through them.

Location:
codecentric AG

title: #2 - Introduction to the tidyverse
description:
Dear all,

We’re happy to invite you to the second meetup of R-Ladies Frankfurt group on 23rd May (Thursday).

This event is going to be a tutorial in which we’re going to explore the tidyverse. The tidyverse is a collection of R packages for data manipulation, exploration, and visualization that share core programming principles. Thus, they are easy to learn and offer basic tools to quickly become an R user.

title: Kick-off meeting R-Ladies Frankfurt
description:
Dear all,

Thanks for joining R-Ladies Frankfurt group!

We're happy to invite you to the first meetup on 12th April (Friday).

This meeting is to:
(1) Present R-Ladies and the motivation to create R-Ladies in Frankfurt
(2) Get to know each other
(3) Discuss topics that you are interested to learn, your expectations about the group, and options to get involved with R-Ladies Frankfurt
(4) R-Ladies code of conduct

This event intends to connect the R-Ladies community in Frankfurt (no matter if you are a complete newbie to R, intermediate or professional R-user) in an informal environment. For that, the idea is to meet for coffee, cake, and networking in a coffeehouse in Frankfurt.

Location:
36 Grad
Oppenheimer Landstraße 36
(Schweizer Platz)
60596 Frankfurt

What to bring?
Ideas and motivation to brainstorm, meet people, and have fun to create an active R community for women!

In the meantime, please fill in the following survey to get an idea of your interests and skill-level: https://forms.gle/Afn6U6qvekNxYaLL9 Feel free to fill out the survey even if you cannot make it to the meeting, as this is important to pick speakers and topics that are of most interest to you in future meetings!

If you have any suggestions/questions, please feel free to get in touch: frankfurt@rladies.org

Also, follow R-Ladies Frankfurt on twitter: @RLadiesFRA (https://twitter.com/RLadiesFRA) and stay tuned for R and R-Ladies related tweets!

Know other people interested in R? Bring them along!
Please only RSVP if you can come!

Looking forward to meeting you!

Sandra
